[test continuation]
# gen222 (docs/plans/the-linguistic-glue.md, G2 — symptom #3, "over-literal"): a
# precisation that CONTINUES the previous computation. "and times 3" after "what is 2
# plus 2" means "(2 plus 2) times 3" = 12, not a literal fragment. The implicit left
# operand is the last result, carried KB-first (last_result/1, reflective layer) and
# INFERRED back — never a C field (PRINCIPLES.md). continue_resolve rewrites the turn
# "what is <last_result> <tail>" and re-dispatches to the arithmetic core. Precisations
# chain (12 -> 13). Bilingual EN+IT. A non-arithmetic "and ..." is never hijacked.
> what is 2 plus 2
< 4.
> and times 3
< 12.
> and plus 1
< 13.
> quanto fa 10 meno 4
< 6.
> e per 5
< 30.
